.AVIATION...
(12Z TAFS)
Issued at 436 AM PDT Sun Mar 8 2026

Currently VFR at all terminals. Moderate (40-60%) confidence on sub-
VFR conditions returning to all terminals tonight with the exception
of LVK which has lower probabilities (10-20%). The return of onshore
flow beneath high pressure will allow for a shallow marine layer to
develop. If clouds end up developing in the marine layer, they will
likely be lower than the low-end MVFR that is currently
advertised. Diurnal winds will prevail.

Vicinity of SFO...Currently VFR with southeasterly flow. Low to
moderate confidence on the return of sub-VFR conditions tonight with
the current TAF advertising low-end MVFR. An alternate/best case
scenario for SFO includes a more compressed marine layer of less
than 1,000 feet which will be difficult to penetrate through the San
Bruno Gap. A reasonable worst case scenario is that fog comes to
fruition in the marine layer. Diurnal winds will prevail.

SFO Bridge Approach...Similar to SFO.

Monterey Bay Terminals...Currently VFR with drainage flow at both
terminals. Moderate confidence on sub-VFR conditions returning to
both terminals tonight. Low-end MVFR is advertised in the current
TAFs to begin the downward trend into what will likely become IFR
once guidance/models come into agreement. Diurnal winds will
prevail.

